snippet.textDisplay:
Every single song in Future Nostalgia has a lyric that can be related to the current pandemic:


Future Nostalgia
No matter what you do, I'm gonna get it
(Let’s do our very best not to get the virus tho, everyone stay home plz)

Don't Start Now
Don't show up, don't come out
(Everyone stay the fuck home)

Cool
I'll show you heaven
(RIP to everyone who’ve died so far from COVID-19)

Physical
Baby, keep on dancing like you ain't got a choice
(What else are we going to do at home all day but dance to Dua Lipa’s songs?)

Levitating
If you wanna run away with me, I know a galaxy
And I can take you for a ride
(Me daydreaming about leaving this planet, which is currently in complete chaos)

Pretty Please
Hate it when you leave me unattended
'Cause I miss ya, and I need your love
When my mind is runnin' wild
Could you help me slow it down?
(We’re all missing the people we usually spend time with. Also checking the news regularly is spiking my anxiety)

Hallucinate
I'm losing my mi-mi-mi-mind, mi-mi-mi-mind
Mi-mi-mi-mind, mi-mi-mi-mind
(I think we’re all starting to lose our minds being stuck at home for days)

Love Again
I can't believe there's something left in my chest anymore
(When you realize that the virus has infected your lungs. Shoulda stayed home)

Break My Heart
But when you said, "Hello"
I knew that was the end of it all
(Virus be like “hello, I’m here to infect y’all!” and us be like, “o shit the world is coming to an end”)

Good in Bed
(Quarantine with other people be like,)
We drive each other mad, mad, mad, mad, mad

Boys Will Be Boys
(Looking at corona virus memes to distract myself from the anxiety be like,)
Isn't it funny how we laugh it off to hide our fear

When there's nothing funny here?
